definitions.definition: Frequent repetition of the same behavior ; way of behavior common to many; ordinary manner; habitual practice ; method of doing, living or behaving.
Habitual buying of goods from one same vendor.

subdefinitions.definition: The habitual patrons (i.e. customers ) of a business; business support.

definitions.definition: Long-established practice, considered as unwritten law, and resting for authority on long consent. Compare prescription .

examples: The Ancient Egyptian culture had many distinctive and interesting beliefs and customs ; one custom was the mummification of the dead.

definitions.definition: A custom (made-to-order) piece of art , etc.

main_definition: Frequent repetition of the same behavior ; way of behavior common to many; ordinary manner; habitual practice ; method of doing, living or behaving.
